= Exercise 1.1
Design context-free grammars for the following languages. Note that $n$ and $m$ are natural numbers.


== ${0^n | n >= 0}$, i.e. the set of all strings made of zero or more 0's.


== ${0^n | n >= 1}$, i.e. the set of all strings made of one or more 0's


== ${O^n 1^m | n >= 1 and m >= 1}$, i.e. the set of all strings made of one or more 0's followed by one or more 1's.


== ${0^n 1^n | n >= 1}$, i.e. the set of all strings made by one or more 0's followed by an equal number of 1's.



